                        <provenance>Ownership inscription by <persName>Yaʿaḳov ben Yitsḥaḳ
                                Roman</persName>, dated AM [5]357 (=1596 or 1597 CE) on fol. :
                                <foreign xml:lang="he">"לי אני הצעיר יעקב בכמ"ר יצחק רומאן זלה"ה
                                ... שנ"ז"</foreign>.</provenance>
                        <acquisition>Edward Pococke's collection of oriental MSS (mostly Armenian,
                            Hebrew and Arabic) was purchased by the Library for £800 in 1692 (see
                                <hi rend="italic">Summary Catalogue</hi>, vol. II, p.
                            1008).</acquisition>
                    </history>
